This htmx extension doesn't seem to require a build process. I found the extension version
in the package.json file. To add to RT:

1) Find the extension directory in the htmx-extensions repo on github:

    https://github.com/bigskysoftware/htmx-extensions/tree/main/src/response-targets

2) Click on the response-targets.js file in github, then click the "Raw" button. Then download that content like:

    wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/bigskysoftware/htmx-extensions/refs/heads/main/src/response-targets/response-targets.js

3) I used uglifyjs to minify the file.

     uglifyjs devel/third-party/htmx-ext-response-targets-2.0.1/response-targets.js > share/static/js/response-targets.min.js
